text: Ikukunitama Shrine (生國魂神社, Ikukunitama jinja) is a Shinto shrine located in Tennōji-ku, Osaka Prefecture, Japan. It holds a big festival on September 9. It it used to be a first rank shrine (官幣大社, kanpei taisha) in the Modern system of ranked Shinto Shrines. == Other websites == * Official website * Osaka's Ikukunitama Shrine set to revive ritual for first time in 70 years Category:Myōjin Taisha Category:Kanpei-taisha Category:Beppyo shrines Category:Pages with unreviewed translations Category:Shinto shrines in Osaka Prefecture
title: Ikukunitama Shrine
